</ul></div><h3 class="feedback-header faculty-answer">Accepted Answers:</h3><div class="faculty-answer"><div><div><label for="nad7hMEw7OYe.12.4774255522742272.2">
                <div><link href="https://seek.onlinedegree.iitm.ac.in/static/codemirror/lib/codemirror.css" rel="stylesheet"><link href="https://seek.onlinedegree.iitm.ac.in/modules/code_tags/resources/code_tags.css" rel="stylesheet"></div><code class="codemirror-container-readonly" data-mode="python">def poly(L, x_0):
    psum = 0
    n = len(L)
    for i in range(n):
        psum = psum + L[i] * (x_0 ** i)
    return psum</code><br>
